  &reftitle.examples;

   Inserting multiple rows with db2_execute_many

    The following example prepares an INSERT statement with parameter markers,
    then executes it once for each set of values in the array.



<?php
$insert = 'INSERT INTO animals (id, breed, name, weight) VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)';

$stmt = db2_prepare($conn, $insert);
if ($stmt) {
    $pets = array(
        array(0, 'cat', 'Pook', 3.2),
        array(1, 'dog', 'Peaches', 12.3),
        array(2, 'horse', 'Smarty', 350.0),
    );
    $affected = db2_execute_many($stmt, $pets);
    print "Inserted $affected rows.";
}
?>


   &example.outputs;


Inserted 3 rows.
